UNION ASSURANCE SOCIETY, Limited, Appellant, v. MIAMI JOCKEY CLUB, Appellee. No. 9151. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 19, 1940. For former opinion, see 110 F.2d 81.

Before FOSTER, SIBLEY, and HUT-CHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Since neither of the judges concurring in the opinion desires a rehearing in the above numbered and entitled cause, it is ordered that the petition for a rehearing be, and it is hereby, denied.
